story_text = Array[String](["Cas9 (CRISPR-associated protein 9) is an enzyme that plays a crucial role in the CRISPR-Cas9 gene editing system. Cas9 acts as a DNA nuclease, meaning it can cut DNA at specific locations. It is guided by a short RNA molecule called a guide RNA (gRNA) to recognize and target a specific DNA sequence. Once Cas9 reaches the target sequence, it cuts both strands of DNA, creating a double-stranded break."])
